14/02/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Police made 78 arrests for serious crimes at the weekend in a sweep that spanned the country, the police's main office announced on Sunday (February 13th). The charges included murder, violent theft, producing and dealing drugs, and illegal weapons possession. Authorities also seized drugs that were to be sold. (Top Channel, News 24, Top News, Ora News - 13/02/11)
